PSEUDOCODE:
- A way to represent algorithms in a simplified, human-readable format.
- Not bound by syntax rules of any specific programming language.
- Used for planning and communicating algorithms before actual coding.

CHARACTERISTICS:
- Language-independent
- Focuses on logic rather than implementation details
- Uses natural language mixed with simple programming constructs
- Helps in algorithm design and analysis

COMMON CONVENTIONS:
- UPPERCASE for keywords (IF, ELSE, WHILE, etc.)
- Indentation to show structure
- Simple symbols for operations (+, -, *, /, =, etc.)
- Plain language for describing complex operations

EXAMPLES:

1. Finding the maximum in an array:
    FUNCTION FindMax(array)
         max ← array[0]
         FOR i ← 1 TO length(array) - 1 DO
              IF array[i] > max THEN
                    max ← array[i]
              END IF
         END FOR
         RETURN max
    END FUNCTION

2. Binary search algorithm:
    FUNCTION BinarySearch(array, target)
         left ← 0
         right ← length(array) - 1
         
         WHILE left ≤ right DO
              mid ← (left + right) / 2
              
              IF array[mid] = target THEN
                    RETURN mid
              ELSE IF array[mid] < target THEN
                    left ← mid + 1
              ELSE
                    right ← mid - 1
              END IF
         END WHILE
         
         RETURN -1  // Element not found
    END FUNCTION